subject: p11474065
History: Year old woman with tracheomalacia s/p tracheal stent removal , pulmonary edema pulmonary edema.
Impression: Heart size and mediastinum are stable. Right basal consolidation is even more conspicuous than on the prior study. Left basal consolidation has progressed. Findings are concerning for development of bibasal infection. No pulmonary edema is currently seen. Postsurgical changes in the right hemi thorax are overall stable including subcutaneous air in the right upper chest wall and associated hematoma.
